et Franju's directorial career in the context of his lifelong commitment to France's cinema institutions.'Georges Franju' will be essential reading on Franju, and of great interest to researchers, academics and students in film studies  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMotion picture producers and directors. 4aFilm and Media Studies 2019. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aFranju's cinema.  aFrench film history.  aFédération Internationale des Archives du Film.  aGeorges Franju.  acinematic aesthetics.  acourts métrages.  aeroticism.  agender identities.  alongs métrages.  asexualities.  ashort films.1 aInce, Kate, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152614145340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526141453423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526141453/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles